      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modelling studies for blood pump CFD",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of seven prior published studies examining CFD-based hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps, including the Giersiepen power-law model calibration, Bludszuweit strain-based model comparisons, and the Goubergrits-Affeld experimental correlation. This synthesis consolidates empirical constants, turbulence model selections, and mesh resolution guidance that inform the present model's parameter choices. The aggregate evidence base spans bench-top PIV data, LDV measurements, and clinical hemolysis indices from three independent research groups, providing a robust multi-source foundation for the hemolysis damage model coefficients adopted here."
